---
description: Service layer conventions (business logic)
globs: services/*/src/services/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---
# Services

- Pure business logic. No HTTP or transport concerns.
- Take typed inputs (already validated). Return typed outputs.
- Throw `AppError` subclasses for known failure modes.
- Database access ONLY via repos/models — never call the ORM directly from a service.
- External AI calls (OpenAI) ONLY via the shared core client.
- Side effects (Redis cache, token tracking) must be explicit.
